name: Setubuh Utan 35mm #2
description:
This negative preserves the remnant of the artist's work. Owner are permitted to recreate work through cyanotype (alt- photography) processes. ____ 
Abdi Alam pt.1 exhibits remnants of a weaver’s forest ruminations during his pilgrimage in Merubetiri National Park, 2017 and Gunung Gede Pangrango, 2021. The abandonment of roots, deforestation of a family, and the shedding of change are several extensions of A. Sebastianus’s contemplation throughout his cyanotype prints and woven studies.

For every edition purchased 1 Tree will be planted through Yagasu Foundation (Yayasan Gajah Sumatra), Indonesia.
